# Digital Literacy Infographic – README
Project Overview

This project is a one-page visual infographic created to help students understand the concept of digital literacy and its importance in everyday academic and personal life. The design highlights key aspects such as what digital literacy means, useful digital tools for students, and safe internet practices.

## Tool Used

The infographic was designed using **Canva**, a free and user-friendly online design platform. Canva provides templates, icons, and layout options that make it easy to create visually appealing educational content.

## What the Design Shows

The infographic explains digital literacy in a simple and engaging way. It includes:

* A clear definition of digital literacy
* Examples of useful digital tools (like email, search engines, and collaboration apps)
* Important tips for staying safe online, such as protecting personal information and identifying fake content

The goal is to make the information easy to understand and visually attractive so that students can quickly grasp the key ideas.

## Learning Experience

While creating this design, one interesting challenge was organizing information in a limited space without making it look cluttered. It helped improve my ability to present information clearly and creatively.

